1. Split should be done by `&quot;=&quot;` (or `&quot;\\s*=\\s&quot;` to exclude whitespaces around `=`)&lt;br/&gt;

*Update* Also it is better to provide `limit` argument to [`String::split`](v=https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#split(java.lang.String,int)) to split at the first occurrence of `&quot;=&quot;`, thanks @AndrewF for suggestion!

2. Fix `toMap` collector to use the first element of the array as key and the last as the value; a merge function may be needed if several namesake cookies are possible

```java
Map&lt;String, String&gt; map = cookies.stream()
    .map(ck -&gt; ck.split(&quot;\\s*=\\s*&quot;, 2)) // Stream&lt;String[]&gt;
    .filter(arr -&gt; arr.length &gt; 1) // ignore invalid cookies
    .collect(Collectors.toMap(arr -&gt; arr[0], arr -&gt; arr[1], (v1, v2) -&gt; v1));
```

If there are multiple cookies with the same name, it may be worth to collect them into `Set&lt;String&gt;` thus keeping all unique values.  For this, `Collectors.groupingBy` and `Collectors.mapping`:
```java
Map&lt;String, Set&lt;String&gt;&gt; map2 = cookies.stream()
    .map(ck -&gt; ck.split(&quot;\\s*=\\s*&quot;, 2)) // Stream&lt;String[]&gt;
    .filter(arr -&gt; arr.length &gt; 1) // ignore invalid cookies
    .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(
        arr -&gt; arr[0], 
        Collectors.mapping(arr -&gt; arr[1], Collectors.toSet())
    ));
```

